<solution>
    <p>[+++++++++++++++]</p>
    <p>Sample responses:</p>
<ol>
      <li><ol>
<li>There are 2 rows of students. Each row has 5 students. There are 5 groups of students. Each group has 2 students. or There are 2 bags with 5 apples in each bag. There are 5 bags with 2 apples in each bag.</li>
<li>The first situation is 2 rows of 5, but the second situation is 5 columns of 2. The situations both describe 10 objects.</li>
</ol>
      </li>
      <li><ol>
<li>
<m>2\times5=10</m> and <m>5\times2=10</m>
</li>
<li>The 5 and the 2 are switched in the second equation just like the rows and columns are switched. The product is the same.</li>
</ol>
      </li>
    </ol>
  </solution>


